<br>
Take Eris for example, the girl would tatoo your name on her arse if you offered to marry her in return. Ask Hectate, she'll back me up on that one ::smiles and nods knowingly::<br>
<br>
::stands and takes his hand:: Take me to your chambers my husband, so that you may welcome me home properly ::smiles coyly:: You can give me something that'll really  give those envious goddesses and mortal women something to jealous about. ::giggles:: And we'll make Aphrodite ever so proud of us ::laughs:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/12/01 2:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> ::Hades smirked slightly as he stood up, still holding his bride in his arms.  He started walked towards his private bed chambers as he looked her in the eyes::<br>
<br>
&quot;So the Olympian women are just like mortal women in the fact they are only interested in wealth and power.&quot;  ::He smirks:: &quot;Figures.  But regardless, my eyes belong only to you.  So yes, let us go and 'embrace' eachother properly.  I have missed you, Persephone.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that he enters the bed chamber, still has her in his arms.  He shuts the door behind him...:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/13/01 3:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> ::Lays in bed nude with Hades few hours later, soft low candles are burning and the smell of exotic incence floats around in the room. Snuggles into his big strong arms smiling with her eyes closed, swirling her forefinger around a bit of his chest hair and laying her head on his chest::<br>
<br>
Mmmmm....oh hades....That was so incredible.. You move faster than Poseidon ::laughs:: Just kidding....<br>
<br>
I was thinking. Why don't we hold a gala? In your honor, or in some kind of honor, inviting all the gods and goddesses everywhere down here. We could have it in the Elysian Fields. What do you think, can we Hades, please? ::looks up at him with her big beautiful eyes pleadingly:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/16/01 6:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> ::Hades lied back in bed, his head on the pillow.  His eyes staring at the ceiling.  He was listening to his wife's voice which sounded like music to him::<br>
<br>
&quot;A gala in the Elysian fields?  No.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He rolled over, absolutly hating to refuse his wife anything, and unable to look her in the eyes after doing so.  But he simply could not allow the gods to gather in his realm.  They shunned him, and he spent as little time with them as possible.::<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sorry, but I cannot allow it.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/16/01 7:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Disappointed</span><hr size=1> ::looks at him as he rolls over, her eyes canot even hide the hurt :: <br>
<br>
W-why not? D-did I do something wrong?....Hades?<br>
<br>
::moves her hand gently to touch his shoulder, but thinks better of it and retracts her hand.her eyes gently cloud over with tears at his sudden mood. Nonetheless, she holds them in as best she could. Gets up and slips on a white thin robe and walks into the living room and shuts the door behind her. A few moments later, her soft dainty weeps can be heard:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/17/01 1:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> ::Hades gets out of bed and doesn't even bother robing himself.  He walks out to the living room to find her.  He looks at her with a hint of compassion in his eyes.  He is about to speak and say something when he closes his mouth and says somthing completely different::<br>
<br>
&quot;Persephone, you have to stop thinking in terms of something 'you' did wrong.  You did nothing wrong.  I just cannot have the Olympians, oither than the ones already accepted here, running around here.  Even for a Party.  I'm sorry.  To much chaos.  To disturbing to the order that is down here.&quot;<br>
